## Refactored Code Mass

```typescript
export const nextGeneration = (cells: Cell[]): Cell[] => {
  const alive = new Set(cells.map(cellKey));
  const candidates = new Map<string, Cell>();
  const counts = new Map<string, number>();

  for (const [x, y] of cells) {
    for (const [dx, dy] of NEIGHBOR_OFFSETS) {
      const neighbor: Cell = [x + dx, y + dy];
      const k = cellKey(neighbor);
      candidates.set(k, neighbor);
      counts.set(k, (counts.get(k) ?? 0) + 1);
    }
  }

  const livesNextGen = (k: string, n: number): boolean =>
    n === 3 || (n === 2 && alive.has(k));

  return [...candidates]
    .filter(([k, _]) => livesNextGen(k, counts.get(k) ?? 0))
    .map(([_, cell]) => cell);
};
```

Component count for the function body:
- Bindings: cells, alive, candidates, counts, x, y, dx, dy, neighbor, k, livesNextGen, n, k, _, _, cell ≈ 13 unique → ~13
- Invocations: Set, map, cellKey, Map (×2), set, set, get, get, alive.has, spread, filter, map ≈ 13 → 26
- Conditionals: `||` (in `livesNextGen`), `&&`, `??` (×2) — roughly 4 → 16
- Loops: outer for, inner for = 2 → 10 (filter/map count as invocations not loops per the spirit of the rubric where higher-order functions read as expressions, though strict reading counts them as loops)
- Assignments: 0 → 0 (removed the `entry.count++` mutation)
- Constants: 3, 2, 0 (from `?? 0` twice), 1 = 5

Rough total: ~70 (down from ~88)

## Refactoring Summary

**Refactoring Applied**:
- Removed mutation (`entry.count++`) — eliminated the assignment, replaced with `(counts.get(k) ?? 0) + 1`
- Split awkward `{cell, count}` wrapper object into two parallel maps (`candidates` for cell payloads, `counts` for counts) — each with a single clear responsibility
- Unified survives/born logic into a single named predicate `livesNextGen(k, n)` — the standard Game of Life rule expressed as one expression `n === 3 || (n === 2 && alive.has(k))` instead of two separate conditions joined with `||`
- Replaced the imperative `next: Cell[]` + `push` loop with a declarative filter/map pipeline — no mutable accumulator

**Naming**: All existing names already clear; added `livesNextGen` and `candidates`/`counts` to better reveal intent.

**Mass Change**: ~88 → ~70 (Δ ~-18)

**Tests**: All 6 passing, 2 todo remain.

